I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve the API data as the first step in our workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll use the data_processing_validator tool to validate the API data we fetched. Since we need a schema for validation, I'll use a default schema that checks for basic JSON structure.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {"type": "array"},
      "status": {"type": "string"}
    },
    "required": ["data", "status"]
  },
  "data": {
    "status": "completed",
    "tool": "network_fetcher",
    "timestamp": "2025-08-27T20:43:05.274593",
    "execution_context": {
      "step": 0,
      "total_tools_executed": 0
    }
  },
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Since the network_fetcher operation failed, I'll attempt to retry the API fetch with the same parameters but with an increased timeout and retry count.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 60,
  "retry_count": 5,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll modify the network_fetcher call to include the required CSV format in the options parameter, as indicated by the error message.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 60,
  "retry_count": 5,
  "options": {
    "format": "csv"
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now that we've successfully fetched the CSV data, I'll proceed with the next step: validating the data structure. I'll use the data_processing_validator tool with a CSV schema.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "headers": {"type": "array"},
      "rows": {"type": "array"}
    },
    "required": ["headers", "rows"]
  },
  "data": {
    "status": "completed",
    "tool": "network_fetcher",
    "timestamp": "2025-08-27T20:46:53.201280",
    "execution_context": {
      "step": 3,
      "total_tools_executed": 1
    }
  },
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            The data validation step appears to have completed successfully. Now I'll proceed with the final step: transforming the data into the specified format using the data_processing_transformer tool.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "csv",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "status": "completed",
    "tool": "network_fetcher",
    "timestamp": "2025-08-27T20:47:11.864628",
